SUMMARY:Morning Sound Bath - Be Well Community Wellness Day
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Be Well']\\nCategory: Training/Workshop\\nStart
  your morning off with a relaxing sound bath focused on your well-being wi
 th local sound bath practitioner Shaun Collins.  Open to all students\, f
 aculty\, staff\, and campus community members. During this soundscape you 
 will be guided along a soothing sound healing journey.From African drummin
 g to Tibetan singing bowls sound has been used to guide and heal the body
  for centuries! This is a deeply immersive full-body experience where vib
 rations are transmitted to your body from various sound healing instrument
 s. Allowing you to comfortably bask in the waves of harmonic sound. All y
 ou have to do is simply rest\, be present\, and allow your body to drift a
 long a beautiful soundscape journey. Part of the 2nd Annual Be Well Commu
 nity Wellness Day!\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEm
 bed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1379756514
LOCATION:Matchbox Tarble Commons Upper Level
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1379756514
CATEGORIES:Training/Workshop
END:VEVENT
