SUMMARY:Be Well Community Wellness Day - Comfort Caring Canine Therapy Dog 
 Visit
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Be Well']\\nCategory: Training/Workshop\\nMark 
 your calendars for the 2nd annual Be Well Community Wellness Day! Br
 ought to you by partners from across the College\, the 2nd annual Be Well 
 Community Wellness Day is an opportunity for students\, staff\, faculty\, 
 and Swarthmore College community members to participate in a wide range of
  activities\, including yoga\, sound baths\, massages\, drum circles\, foo
 d trucks\, and more! Activities will be taking place all throughout campus
  on April 17th between 9 a.m. and 5 p.m. The Be Well Community Wellness Da
 y will be offering a mix of flexible drop-in activities and special sessio
 ns that require sign-ups. Drop by whenever you need a breather\, and be su
 re to check out the full schedule for more information on session descript
 ions\, timing\, and locations. For questions about accessibility or to req
 uest accommodations\, please email BeWell@swarthmore.edu. Details: For Wh
 o: Students\, Faculty\, Staff\, and Swarthmore community members!When:
  Friday\, April 17th\, 2026 from 9 am - 5 pmWhere: All around campus! (l
 ook out for more details and sign ups coming later this month) What: Mult
 iple events focused on various dimensions of wellness - events range from 
 5-60 minutes (more details coming later)NEW THIS YEAR: All participants wi
 ll be entered into a raffle to win an incentive of their choice!  The mor
 e events you attend\, the more entries you will receive. At the end of the
  day\, 150 participants will be selected as winners and notified the follo
 wing week.   \\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed
 =view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1383880849
LOCATION:Isabelle Cosby Courtyard\, Kohlberg Coffee Bar Commons\, Kohlberg 
 Breezeway
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1383880849
CATEGORIES:Training/Workshop
END:VEVENT
