SUMMARY:Hands-Only CPR Session
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Other'\, 'Be Well']\\nCategory: Student Group M
 eeting/Practice\\nPush to Save: Hands-Only CPR TrainingJoin us for Push to
  Save\, a free community training where you will learn hands-only CPR\, a 
 simple skill that can double or even triple a person’s chance of surviva
 l during sudden cardiac arrest. In just 45 minutes\, participants will lea
 rn how to recognize cardiac arrest\, perform effective chest compressions\
 , and respond quickly in an emergency.Location: Matchbox Fitness Center\, 
 3rd FloorDate: April 18Session Times:• 2:00–2:45 PM• 2:45–3:30 PM
 • 3:30–4:15 PM• 4:15–5:00 PMThis event is free and open to the com
 munity. Learn a skill that can save a life!\\nDetails: https://swatcentral
 .swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1379655787
LOCATION:Matchbox Tarble Commons Upper Level
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1379655787
