SUMMARY:SwatTalk: Alumni Author Jamie Madden ’06
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['College Advancement']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel
  Discussion\\nSwatTalk: Jamie Madden ’06 Monday\, April 20\, 2026 at 8:0
 0 p.m. RSVP Join Jamie Madden ’06 in conversation with moderator Twan Cl
 aiborne ’07 about his recently published memoir Bittersweet Lane: Creati
 ng Home(s) in the American Affordable Housing Crisis. We’ll discuss the 
 nature of the housing crisis\, what is necessary to solve it\, and the rol
 e of lived experience in the professional and academic worlds. Jamie Madde
 n ’06 wrote Bittersweet Lane: Creating Home(s) in the American Affordabl
 e Housing Crisis to demystify affordable housing while exploring the meani
 ng of home from an intergenerational\, lower-class perspective. Jamie grew
  up in affordable housing at the Bittersweet Lane Apartments and went on t
 o work for the affordable housing industry’s leading nonprofits. He is a
  dad\, a community development professional\, and a Truman Scholar. He hol
 ds degrees from MIT and Swarthmore College. Jamie's work has helped create
  more than 1\,000 affordable homes. SwatTalks is an Alumni Council initiat
 ive that engages the broader Swarthmore community through seminars featuri
 ng alumni and faculty members excelling in their fields. Each hour-long on
 line seminar is free and open to Swarthmore alumni\, families\, faculty\, 
 staff\, students\, and friends. We welcome suggestions for future speakers
  and topics — please email your ideas to alumni@swarthmore.edu.\\nDetai
 ls: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid
 %3D1390294701
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1390294701
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
