SUMMARY:“What’s in a (Building’s) Name?”
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Meeting\\n“Wha
 t’s in a (Building’s) Name?”Scheuer Room\, Kohlberg HallApril 22\, 4
 :30-6:00 p.m. Panelists:  Lisa Alvarez-Cohen\, Vice Provost for Academic P
 lanning\, UC BerkeleyErin Brownlee Dell\, Chief of Staff and Secretary of 
 the College\, Swarthmore CollegeKimberly Wright Cassidy ’85\, H’25\, N
 inth President\, Bryn Mawr CollegeRoberta “Bobbi” Cordano\, President\
 , Gallaudet University Moderator: Catherine "Cat" Norris\, Associate Dean
  of the Faculty for Academic Programs and Research\, Swarthmore College  
 Description: This is the third in a series of events on the renaming of Ol
 d Science Hall.  Lisa Alvarez-Cohen\, an environmental engineer whose res
 earch focuses on the application of microbiological processes for the elim
 ination of environmental contaminants\, was named Berkeley’s vice provos
 t for academic planning in 2018. Last year\, Berkeley chose an Indigenous 
 name for a campus building and consulted with Indigenous people in the pro
 cess. Kimberly Wright Cassidy ’85\, H’25\, joined Bryn Mawr’s psycho
 logy faculty in 1993 and served as its ninth president from 2013-2024. Dur
 ing her tenure as president\, she oversaw the renaming of Bryn Mawr’s li
 brary.   Cat Norris is Associate Dean of the Faculty for Academic Progra
 ms and Research and an associate professor of psychology. She joined Swar
 thmore’s faculty in 2013.First event:April 1 – Anatomy of a Shadow Eco
 nomy: Body Snatching and the Making of American MedicineSecond event:April
  15 – Old Science Hall Renaming Task Force: Our Charge and Process\, Com
 munity Survey Results\, and Q&AFourth event:April 29 – Lenape: Resilienc
 e\, Return\, and Renewal\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?tr
 umbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1382122033
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1382122033
CATEGORIES:Meeting
END:VEVENT
