SUMMARY:Swarthmore Night at Lincoln Center Theater: Ragtime
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['College Advancement']\\nCategory: Film/Movie\\n
 An unforgettable story\, told on one of New York's greatest stages. Swarth
 more Night at Lincoln Center Theater: Ragtime 6:15 p.m. Lincoln Center The
 ater150 W 65th StreetNew York$69 per person This event has reached capacit
 y. To be added to a waitlist\, please contact alumni@swarthmore.edu.We’r
 e coming together to experience Ragtime\, a breathtaking musical adaptatio
 n of E.L. Doctorow’s celebrated novel. The story beautifully weaves toge
 ther the lives of three fictional families — a Black pianist and his bel
 oved\; a Jewish immigrant and his daughter\; and a wealthy white family 
 — all in pursuit of the American Dream at the dawn of the 20th century. 
 Space for this event is extremely limited\, and we expect it to fill up qu
 ickly. If you're thinking about joining us\, don't wait — reserve your d
 iscounted loge ticket today. Program 6:15 p.m. — Lobby Opens: Follow the
  signage to meet fellow Swatties in our private gathering area\, the Patro
 n Room\, to collect your tickets and name tags before the show. Tickets wi
 ll be available in this room until showtime. 6:30 p.m. — Mix\, Mingle\, 
 & Learn: We'll have a special opportunity to hear from Jenna Clark Embrey\
 , LCT's Literary Manager and Dramaturg\, in conversation with Kathy Liu 
 ’04\, LCT’s Director of Development. 7:00 p.m. — Showtime: Take your
  seats for Ragtime. The performance runs 2 hours and 50 minutes\, includin
 g one intermission.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaE
 mbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1385489003
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1385489003
CATEGORIES:Film/Movie
END:VEVENT
