SUMMARY:Joyland Screening
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Interfaith Center']\\nCategory: Film/Movie\\nSw
 atties of South Asia (SOSA) and Interfaith Center are hosting a film scree
 ning of Joyland\, a film that follows Haider\, a gentle\, quiet man living
  within the constraints of a traditional joint family. When he secretly ta
 kes a job at an erotic dance theater\, Haider becomes captivated by Biba\,
  a bold and magnetic transgender performer. As their relationship deepens\
 , Haider is pulled between desire and duty\, while the women in his househ
 old struggle with their own forms of confinement.\\nDetails: https://swatc
 entral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1389756395
LOCATION:Martin Hall 028 Ping and Rose Chen Screening Room\, Martin Hall Te
 rrace\, Martin Hall 028 Lobby\, Martin Hall 025 Kitchen
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1389756395
CATEGORIES:Film/Movie
END:VEVENT
