DTEND:20260429T220000Z
SUMMARY:Lenape: Resilience\, Return\, and Renewal
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Meeting\\nJeremy
  Johnson\, Cultural Education Director\, Delaware Tribe of Indians (Lenape
 )Scheuer Room\, Kohlberg Hall April 29\, 4:30-6:00 p.m. Description: This 
 is the fourth and final event in a series on the renaming of Old Science H
 all. In this talk\, Johnson examines the deep history of the Lenape people
  in their ancestral homelands and the profound impacts of displacement thr
 ough colonial expansion and forced removal. It traces how\, despite these 
 disruptions\, the Lenape have sustained cultural continuity through langua
 ge\, traditions\, and the transmission of knowledge across generations.The
  presentation highlights ongoing efforts to return - physically\, cultural
 ly\, and spiritually – to Lënapehokink\, emphasizing initiatives that 
 restore presence\, strengthen community ties\, and renew relationships to 
 land. Centering both historical realities and contemporary leadership\, it
  underscores how resilience and acts of return continue to shape Lenape id
 entity and future pathways grounded in sovereignty\, connection\, and rene
 wal. Jeremy Johnson is the cultural education director of the Delaware Tri
 be of Indians\, based in Bartlesville\, Okla. He is Lenape\, Absentee Shaw
 nee\, and Peoria. Prior to his current role\, he served as assistant chief
  of the Delaware Tribe. A lifelong educator\, he is committed to preservin
 g and revitalizing Lenape culture and language for the future generations 
 of his tribe.  All events are sponsored by the Swarthmore College Preside
 nt’s Office.Past events:First event:April 1 – Anatomy of a Shadow Econ
 omy: Body Snatching and the Making of American Medicine Second event:Apri
 l 15 – Old Science Hall Renaming Task Force: Our Charge and Process\, Co
 mmunity Survey Results\, and Q&AThird event:April 22 – “What’s in a 
 (Building’s) Name?”\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?tru
 mbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1382122034
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1382122034
CATEGORIES:Meeting
END:VEVENT
