SUMMARY:Swarthmore College Chinese Music Ensemble
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Music Department'\, 'Music and Dance']\\nCatego
 ry: Performance\\nThe Chinese Music Ensemble\, co-directed by Guowei Wang 
 and Lei Ouyang\, performs traditional and contemporary music from differen
 t regions of China\, Hong Kong\, Taiwan\, and the Chinese Diaspora. Studen
 ts perform on traditional Chinese instruments including the guzheng (zithe
 r)\, erhu (bowed fiddle)\, pipa (plucked lute)\, yangqin (hammered dulcime
 r)\, dizi (flute)\, and percussion.  This performance will be streamed l
 ive.  Swarthmore College encourages persons with disabilities to particip
 ate in its programs and activities. If you anticipate needing any type of 
 accommodation or have questions about the physical access provided\, pleas
 e contact Susan Smythe\, ADA Program Manager at 610-690-2063 in advance of
